      <p class="text-center text-gray-600 mt-4 text-sm">Refined Ideas</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="portfolio-section mt-16">
    <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8 portfolio-text">Drafting a Design</h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl portfolio-text">Once we had the basic ideas and sketches we moved on to creating a first draft of our design for both the mobile app and the mirror overlay. We were pressed for time, and so when we started making greybox wireframes, one of my teammates made the executive decision to go straight to hi-fi.</p>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mt-4 portfolio-text">One of the first issues we faced was how the different clothing should be presented on the app and the mirror that would be cohesive and easily understood.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-12">
    <div class="portfolio-image portfolio-image-left">
      <img src="https://placehold.co/300x500?text=Original+Mirror" alt="Original mirror design" class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-lg" />
      <p class="text-center text-gray-600 mt-4 text-sm">Original Mirror Home</p>
    </div>
    <div class="portfolio-image portfolio-image-right">
      <img src="https://placehold.co/300x500?text=Mobile+Design" alt="Mobile design" class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-lg" />
      <p class="text-center text-gray-600 mt-4 text-sm">Mobile Home</p>
    </div>
    <div class="portfolio-image portfolio-image-left">
      <img src="https://placehold.co/300x500?text=Updated+Design" alt="Updated design" class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-lg" />
      <p class="text-center text-gray-600 mt-4 text-sm">Updated Home</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="portfolio-section mt-16">
    <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8 portfolio-text">Usability Testing</h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl portfolio-text">We did some usability testing. I created a script with six tasks for users to try and complete. Reactions were really positive to the concept of the product.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="my-12 bg-gray-50 p-8 rounded-lg portfolio-section">
    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 portfolio-text">Key Findings</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-4 text-lg text-gray-700 portfolio-text">
      <li class="flex items-start">
        <span class="font-bold mr-4 text-blue-600">1.</span>
        <span>Users have a really hard time finding the '+' button to add an item of clothing to today's outfit.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start">
        <span class="font-bold mr-4 text-blue-600">2.</span>
        <span>Most users did not figure out that the row of clothes for today's outfit was scrollable horizontally.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start">
        <span class="font-bold mr-4 text-blue-600">3.</span>
        <span>When it comes to checking the calendar on Mobile, users had a hard time telling what things meant.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start">
        <span class="font-bold mr-4 text-blue-600">4.</span>
        <span>The weather screen on the mirror was poorly organized, with users thinking that both columns were part of the same set.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="portfolio-section mt-16">
    <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8 portfolio-text">Revisions</h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl portfolio-text">I went through and moved the '+' button to the front of the row on the home screen of the mirror. I also completely redid the weather page for the mirror after consulting with ChatGPT and exploring other interfaces' weather pages.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-8 my-12">
    <div class="portfolio-image portfolio-image-left">
      <img src="https://placehold.co/400x600?text=Original+Weather" alt="Original weather page" class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-lg" />
      <p class="text-center text-gray-600 mt-4 text-sm">Original Weather Page</p>
    </div>
    <div class="portfolio-image portfolio-image-right">
      <img src="https://placehold.co/400x600?text=Updated+Weather" alt="Updated weather page" class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-lg" />
      <p class="text-center text-gray-600 mt-4 text-sm">Final Weather Page</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="portfolio-section mt-16">
    <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8 portfolio-text">Takeaways</h2>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg portfolio-text">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-2">ChatGPT as Design Advisor</h3>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">ChatGPT can be a valuable design advisor, as long as you keep in mind the role it plays in the bigger picture.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg portfolio-text">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-900 mb-2">Team Communication</h3>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700">Communication among group members can make design faster and better. I had a breakthrough when I adopted my teammate's strategy.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
`,
